      • createSessionPort

        public static <P> P createSessionPort(String url,
                                      String sessionId,
                                      Service service,
                                      Class portType)
        Create a usable session port including a URL and session id.
        Type Parameters:
        P - the type of session port to create.
        Parameters:
        url - the URL for the port.
        sessionId - the session id to use for the SOAP header.
        service - the service to call.
        portType - used to retrieve a port from the service.
        Returns:
        a usable port that has session id and URL set.

      • createSessionPort

        public static <P> P createSessionPort(WebServiceType webServiceType,
                                      LoginContext loginContext,
                                      Service service,
                                      Class portType)
        Create a usable session port - the session id an url are pulled from loginContext.
        Type Parameters:
        P - the type of session port to create.
        Parameters:
        webServiceType - the type of web service that will be called..
        loginContext - a previously log in - contains the URL and session id to make the web service call.
        service - the service to call.
        portType - used to retrieve a port from the service.
        Returns:
        a usable port that has session id and URL set.

      • createSessionPort

        public static <P> P createSessionPort(ApiWebService apiWebService,
                                      LoginContext loginContext)
        Create a usable session port - the session id an url are pulled from loginContext.
        Type Parameters:
        P - the type of session port to create.
        Parameters:
        apiWebService - one of the built in SFDC web service types.
        loginContext - a previously log in - contains the URL and session id to make the web service call.
        Returns:
        a usable port that has session id and URL set.
